SHURTAPE TECHNOLOGIES, LLC SUED 3M IN THE U.S. DISTRICT COURT FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF NORTH CAROLINA, ALLEGING THAT 3MS SCOTCHBLUE PAINTERS MASKING TAPE WITH EDGE-LOCK PAINT LINE PROTECTOR, WHICH WAS INTRODUCED IN LATE 2009, INFRINGES SHURTAPES U.S. PATENT DESCRIBING MASKING TAPE HAVING AN ABSORBENT COATING APPLIED TO THE EDGE OF THE TAPE AND SEVERAL OF SHURTAPES TRADEMARKS. 3M CHALLENGED BOTH SHURTAPES ALLEGATIONS OF INFRINGEMENT AND THE VALIDITY OF THE PATENT. IN SEPTEMBER 2013, THE

